  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Corruption Free administration and Allocation 2% of the District Assembly Common Fund for Persons wi</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">5,200 Persons With Disability are aware of their right to and the amount of the 2% District Assembly Common Fund (DACF) due persons with disability.
2. Corrupt practices related to the disbursement of the 2% DACF meant for persons with disability are reduced by 70%.
3. Persons with disability are receiving their share of the 2% DACF in the right amount and at the right time without any artificial barriers.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Project Launching,
2. Baseline data collection
3. Sensitisation workshops for PWDs and District assembly staff.
4. Interface meetings with Persons with disability and District Assembly staff (Duty bearers)
5. Media engagement and Advocacy.
6. Dialogue and consultative meetings with Social Services Sub-committee of District Assemblies.
7. Quarterly Review and Learning Meetings.
8. Monitoring and Evaluation. 
9. Documentation and Reporting</narrative>
  </description>
